{
  "stem": "1354.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Like I said in the-- in the book  there, that before Schindler saved me, he saved me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because if he wouldn't take us out from Wieliczka at that time, none of us would survive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right after the-- after the war, because we still were hoping to see, when we came to Krakow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First thing, we went to the house there where we lived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had a janitor what-- there what we were friendly with her.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and when she saw me, and she said, oh, my god.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From all of them, you lived through?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You're such a quiet one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was meant to be.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was-- I guess it was meant to be.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And your sister, who was taken away from Auschwitz in the other direction, what happened to her?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From Auschwitz-- oh yeah, she-- she's OK.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She-- after the-- when we came to Krakow, I found out that she's-- she's already there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she had that little girl.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or my little-- the little girl-- I forgot to tell you that, in ghetto, before-- before they took my mother, when I went for that night shift, my brother arranged.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he took out the-- handed the girl to a Gentile family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she lived through.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She lives now.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She's over 50 years old now.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She lives in Camarillo.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Unfortunately, she's sick, but-- but she lived through.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and then, my sister got together-- her husband lived through too, because he was with us in Brinnlitz.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then, in 1946, I-- after six months knowing my husband, we got married, and--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Krakow.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was in my sister's house, that I gave you the-- some-- some picture.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "May 19, 1946.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after six months, there started to be already pogroms, believe it or not.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
